meta {
  name: Clone Site Admin Template
  type: http
  seq: 17
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/lab-tests/{{siteAdminLabTestId}}/clone
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{businessAccessToken}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "masterDataId": "{{masterDataId}}"
  }
}

script:post-response {
  const data = res.getBody() && res.getBody().data;
  if (data && data.id) bru.setEnvVar("clonedLabTestId", data.id);
}

docs {
  Clone a SITE_ADMIN lab-test template (the `:id` in the URL) into the caller's
  tenant catalogue. Business JWT. **Only `masterDataId` is sent in the body** —
  `tenantId`/`branchId` come from the JWT and the target master data, never the
  client (CLAUDE.md §4.7). Captures `clonedLabTestId`.

  Behaviour: deep-copies the template + its samples, result params, and each
  param's reference ranges/values with fresh UUIDs, sets `source = "TENANT"`,
  `tenantId` (JWT), `branchId` (from the master data), `masterDataId` (body), and
  seeds a fresh `versionHistory` v1. Fully transactional — any failure rolls back
  with no partial rows.

  - `siteAdminLabTestId` is a live SITE_ADMIN template → else 404
    `LAB_TEST_NOT_FOUND`.
  - `masterDataId` must belong to the caller's tenant → else 404
    `MASTER_DATA_NOT_FOUND`.
  - 409 `LAB_TEST_NAME_CONFLICT` / `LAB_TEST_CODE_CONFLICT` if the template's
    name/code already exists (active) in the target master data.
}
